
Definition
Sock puppets are fake online personas created for specific purposes, such as gathering information or influencing online discussions.

Creation
Secure emails, anonymous profiles, and careful selection of online personas are essential for creating effective sock puppets.

Maintenance
Maintaining consistency, avoiding linking real data, and staying aware of detection risks are crucial for sock puppet management.









